She studied Political Science at Eastern Illinois University, where she gained the foundational knowledge that supports her work as a public servant. A strong community is key to her role in leadership, and she is passionate about fostering small business growth, recognizing its vital importance to the ever-expanding community she serves.

In her former professional capacity, she served as the Director of Marketing and Public Relations for locally owned marketing businesses based in St. Peters. Her career is grounded in entrepreneurial experience, having owned and operated businesses, which has driven her active participation in both professional and philanthropic community boards.

